            <h2>FAQs</h2>
            <h3>How many active terminals does LaGuardia Airport have?</h3>
            <p>LaGuardia Airport has three active terminals: A, B, and C.</p>
            <h3>What is the main feature of Terminal A?</h3>
            <p>Terminal A, known as the Marine Air Terminal, was originally designed for overseas flights and served Pan American Airways' flying boats.</p>
            <h3>Who manages Terminal B?</h3>
            <p>Terminal B is managed by LaGuardia Gateway Partners, a private company.</p>
            <h3>What recent developments have occurred at Terminal B?</h3>
            <p>Terminal B has undergone a multi-billion dollar redesign, resulting in a new terminal with two gate concourses: the Western Concourse (Gates 11–31) and Eastern Concourse (Gates 40–59).</p>
            <h3>What amenities are available in the terminals?</h3>
            <p>The terminals offer various amenities, including dining options, shopping, lounges, and free Wi-Fi.</p>
            <h3>Are the terminals connected?</h3>
            <p>Yes, the terminals are connected by shuttle buses and walkways.</p>
            <h3>What airlines currently operate out of Terminal A?</h3>
            <p>As of now, Terminal A is primarily used by Spirit Airlines.</p>
            <h3>What is unique about Terminal C?</h3>
            <p>Terminal C encompasses the old Terminals C and D and features four gate concourses.</p>
            <h3>How can passengers navigate between terminals?</h3>
            <p>Passengers can navigate between terminals using shuttle buses and walkways that connect them.</p>
            <h3>What kind of transportation options are available to reach LaGuardia Airport?</h3>
            <p>Transportation options include taxis, ride-sharing services (like Uber and Lyft), shuttle services, and public transit.</p>




